review_blob: On tap at BZs, pours black with a thing light tan head. Aroma is sweet cream and vanilla with light roast. Flavor is roasted malt, burnt sugars, vanilla bean and sweet cream. Solid! Hey, I rated a beer!

First to rate! From a growler thanks to Sherman Gallup!! Pours deep amber with a thin tan head, good lacing. Aroma is toast and nutty malts through and through. Really clean aroma. Flavor is nice and balanced with a good hop kick on the back end. Big toast and light caramel with bitter nuts and grassy hops finishing dry. Not bad at all. Thanks again Sherman!!

Bottle thanks to Tim, pours deep ruby brown with a medium off white head. Aroma is super malty and fruity with plums and figs. Really Belgian smelling. Flavor is sweet caramel malts, bread, French toast. Really nice beer. Nice!!
Growler thanks to Tim, pours ruby red with a thin tan head. Aroma is bread through and through. Really deep malty nose. Flavor is big toast and bread with a light citrus finish. Well balanced.

Bottle pours hazy orange with a medium frothy white head. Aroma is metallic, citrus, chemical. Flavor is sweet upfront but very offensive in the finish with way too much carbonation. Very astringent old hop flavor that was easily a drain pour.
beer_name: Phoenix Ale Hoppy Valley Ale - Session IPA

review_blob: Bottle pours straw yellow with a thin white head. Aroma is clean grains and grassy hops. Flavor is again clean pale straw and peppery slightly soapy hops. Yes please!
Bottle pours murky brown with a thin tan head and massive amounts of carbonation causing a gusher. Smells and tastes old and infected. Citrus butter bomb. Not pleasant.
beer_name: HeBrew Genesis Dry Hopped Session Ale

review_blob: Bottle pours orange with a thin white head.  Aroma and flavor are tart orange and citrus fruit through and through.  Either old or very one dimensional.

Really liked this one.  Bottle from liberty tap room pours deep ruby with a medium tan head.  Big spicy rye notes with dank hops.  Flavor is big roasty and rye with nice earthy bitterness in the finish.
Straight forward mild.  Fruity aromas and flavors with clean toast and nutty malts.  Nice beer.
On tap at 1702, pours completely black with a medium light tan head.  Aroma is big and roasty.  Flavor is thick and creamy with tons of roast and burnt malts.
beer_name: Oskar Blues Nitro Smidy Black Lager

review_blob: On tap at 1702, pours hazy deep yellow with no head.  Aroma is clean wheat with a bit of a sweet lemon element in the background.  Flavor is awesome.  Big cracked wheat and crackers with pale grain and big sour citrus notes in the finish.  Excellent.

bottle pours orange with a thin white head.  Aroma is bready and slightly sour in a citrus way.  Flavor is very malt forward, but again there is a slight sourness that I dont think is intentional.  Eh.

Um, where to begin.  I loved this stuff.  Its a nicely made saison, low in alcohol and comes in a can.  Could this stuff be made year round?  Pours hazy bright yellow with a medium white head.   Aroma is big phenolic saison yeast with touches of light lemongrass.  Flavor is much the same.  Refreshing as hell, lots of hay and grassy malts with light spice touches matching up well with the lemongrass elements.  A nice pairing both brewery and ingredient wise.  Cheers!!

bottle pours straw yellow with a medium white head.  Aroma is actually really nice, big tropical fruit hops.  Loads of mango and pineapple.  Flavor is nice and light upfront with crackers and grassy malts ending with a light but again tropical fruit bitterness.  Almost like guava.  Really neat and simple beer.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Citra Blonde Summer Brew

review_blob: Good stuff.  Deep hazy amber, tons of lacing in the creamy tan head.  Aroma and flavors are a nice balanced mix of toffee and breaded malts, nice earthy hop finish drying out the mouth.  Very nice beer!
beer_name: Samuel Adams Tasman Red Red IPA

review_blob: Bottle pours hazy dark orange with a thin white head.  Aroma is grainy, wheat, crackers.  Flavor is watery, thin wheat, some thin peach notes. Eh.....
beer_name: Spanish Peaks Chugs Private Stash Big Bite Peach Wheat

review_blob: Bottle, pours black with a medium dark brown head, fades quickly to a light film.  Aroma is big roast and cocoa.  Flavor is much the same, big roast, black strap molasses and burnt sugars.  Semi sweet cocoa finishes with a little smoke.  Really nice stuff with just the right amount of carbonation.

Bottle pours hazy bright yellow with a medium frothy white head.  Good bits of carbonation shooting up the glass.  Aroma is full of clean pilsner malts, grassy, with spicy and skunky hops.  Flavor is crisp and clean pale malts, crackers, bits of toast.  The hops are a let down in the finish.  No bite or spicy finish.  Its very malt forward.

On tap at SanTan, Chandler, pours light golden yellow with a medium white head.  Well hello you sexy American Pale!  Aroma is big tropical and citrus.  Think mango and pineapple with dare I say it watermelon!  Irresistible aroma.  Flavor does not disappoint with a nice clean pale grass malt bill letting these juicy and insanely dank hops shine.  Stunning pale.  Wish this was regular canned option as I would drink it in moderation to enjoy its exceptional quality, and pound it because it goes down just that good.
Can, pours light gold with a thin white head.  Aroma is pale grassy grains and light lager yeast.  Flavors of crackers, pale grains, grass.  Very earthy and clean through and through.
Nice white.  Pours hazy light orange with a thin white head, light lacing.  Aroma is big coriander and citrus.  Flavor much the same with a nice balance and clean finish.
Bottle pours light golden color with a thin white head.  Nothing but pale grains and crackers.  Did not enjoy this one very much.  Eh.

Thanks to Tim for the hookup while I was away!  Pours dark copper with a medium cream head and lots of lacing.  Great growler fill, carbonation level is perfect.  Aroma is toast and nutty malts covered with loads of fruity esters.  Flavor is big caramel and toasted malts upfront with very earthy clean hops and a light roast/burnt malt element in the finish.  Really nice beer!

Bottle, pours bright orange with a medium white head.  Aroma is big citrus all around.  Lots of orange.  Flavor is clean with grassy malts and again hops lending  light bitterness and lots of juicy orange flavor.

bottle from table and vine in Springfield, pours hazy bright orange with a 2 finger rocky white head.  Good lacing.  Nose is bright and fresh citrus with some tropical notes as well.  Very fresh and clean aroma.  Flavor is just outstanding.  Perfectly balanced malts and hops.  Nice clean pale grains and crackers without being overly sweet.  Hops are balanced throughout with nice citrus notes ending dry.  I could really drink this stuff all day and its a top 3 pale ale for me.  Great stuff.

bottle from Table and Vine in Springfield MA, bottle says the beer was bottled in Apr of 2013 and its Apr 9th so a very fresh bottle.  Pours deep orange with a rocky off white head that lasts all the way to the bottom.  Lovely looking stuff.  Aroma is all big juicy fresh hop cones.  More pine and skunk than anything, but very bright and wonderful nose.  Flavor is a tad disappointing but still a solid IPA non-the-less.  Big toast and pale grains strangled by bitter, bitter, bitter hops.  A little too heavy handed hops for me, but I still killed the bomber fairly easily and would definitely like to drink this again.
Can pours bright orange with a thin white head.  Aroma is huge green, dank, wet pine hops.  Flavor is pale grains and crackers with a huge dry pine and resinous grassy hop finish.  Damn near perfect.
Can pours light orange with a medium tan head.  Tropical fruit aroma.  Huge grassy malt and hops going on.  Big tropical fruit notes as well.  Enjoyable.
Bottle pours light Amber with a thin white head.  Aroma is dank resinous pine.  Flavor is dry pine hops and toast with nutty notes in the finish.  Very balanced.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Bottle at home, pours light amber with a thin off white head.  Aroma is crystal and Munich malts.  Flavor is light and crisp toasted malts with a clean finish.
On tap at 1702, pours black with a medium tan head, good lacing.  Nice sweet cocoa and roast with a green chile note that is more vegetal than hot.
beer_name: Green Flash Double Stout - Serrano Chilis

review_blob: On tap Sept 12.  Pours light Brown with a thin tan head.  Aroma is bourbon, vanilla and oak.  Flavor is all barrel.  Big bourbon and booze with sweet vanilla.
beer_name: Thunder Canyon Countdown Honey Brown - Barrel Aged

review_blob: On tap 12? Sept, pours black with a medium tan head.  Big bitter cocoa and coffee nose.  Flavor is rich roast and cocoa, mildly sweet with a huge coffee finish.
On tap Sept 2012 pours gold with a medium white head.  Nose is pale grains and white grape juice.  Flavor is same with mild white wine notes.
Very sweet artificial strawberry.  Big in the nose as well.  On tap Sept 12.  Not my thing.

2011 bottle at home, pours hazy brown with reddish hues around the sides of the glass, medium off white head that fades to a thin film that sits the length of the glass.  Aroma is lovely, big floral honey, boozy alcohol, caramel malts, maple.  Flavor is big and malty with still some nice hops balancing things out, but still more malt forward with nuts and sweet caramel ending with only mild alcohol.  Nice!

Bottle, thanks SHIG!  Pours black with a medium tan head.  Aroma is roast, cocoa and light smoke.  Flavor is light and semi-tart like a traditional porter.  Big roast, cocoa nibs, tart cherry in the finish.  Nice and highly drinkable.

bottle pours hazy gold with a medium white head.  Aroma is crisp pale malts and a citrus/estery note that is kind of hard to place.  Flavor is crisp and clean pale malt, crystal and cereals.  Ends with a nice green apple fruity tart yeast flavor.  Very refreshing.

Bottle thanks to Tim, pours motor oil black, and thick as hell too.  Medium dark brown head.  Aroma screams barrel.  Big bourbon, sticky molasses, oak, and chocolate.  Flavor is much the same, there is substantial roast dryness here which is nice standing up to the sweet vanilla bourbon notes that round things out.  Perfect example of a BA imp stout.
beer_name: Hangar 24 Barrel Roll No. 03: Pugachevs Cobra - Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle thanks to Tim, pours bright hazy orange with a medium white head.  Aroma is part cider and part funky yeast.  Flavor is not as funky as the nose leads on but has some Belgian yeast tartness much like the seasonal from this brewery.  Nice clean light malt bill with the fruity/yeast tartness finishing nicely.  I like it.
beer_name: Hangar 24 Barrel Roll No. 02: Humpty Bump - Strong Belgian Golden Ale

review_blob: thanks to Tim for the hookup on this, and in the new 4th Ann glass to boot.  You rock!  Pours dark brown with a huge light tan head that leaves a nice lacing the length of the glass.  Aroma is really nice and have tremendous depth.  Big toast and nutty malts, the rye whiskey is apparent but finessed well as it only complements.  Flavor is extremely rich, caramel and light roast notes blend with nutty character and big wood in the finish.  This is awesome stuff, and one of my favorites from this brewery.
Bottle pours black with a medium tan head.  Aroma is huge coffee and cocoa.  Flavor is sweet cocoa up front but ends with a ton of dry roast.  Bold stuff!
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Imperial Stout

review_blob: bottle in the mixed case pours black with a medium tan head.  Aroma is lactose, big roast and coffee.  Flavor is semi-sweet cocoa and roast with a dry finish.  Nice beer.
beer_name: Big Sky Slow Elk Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Draft at BZs pizza, pours brown with a medium tan head.  Aroma is spiced bread malts, cinnamon and peppery hops.  Flavor is nutty, bread, rye, again spicy hops.  I like it, and its nice with the garlic knots!
beer_name: Big Sky Heavy Horse Scotch Ale

review_blob: Nothing special or offensive here.  Solid wheat beer with sweet citrus notes and pale malts with the wheat make for a refreshing summer brew.  Hooray for cans!!
beer_name: Big Sky Montana Trout Slayer Ale

review_blob: solid brown ale that we now get in cans, so I will be drinking more of it on camping excursions.  Big coffee and dry roasted malt flavor and aroma with a nice dry finish.  Solid Brown!
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Bottle pours hazy orange with a medium fluffy white head.  Aroma is huge orange peel and coriander that almost cover up the booziness of this beer, but the alcohol is there and stings the nose a bit.  Flavor is very sweet and a tad cloying with the spices again being very overpowering but covering up for the ten percent alcohol.  I enjoy a regular wit, this just isnt my thing.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Imperial White

review_blob: Bottle pours brown with a medium light brown head.  Aroma and flavor are awesome.  Huge bread and nutty malt with really nice yeast character in the finish.  This is a home run.
beer_name: Samuel Adams LongShot A Dark Night in Munich

review_blob: Bottle pours dark hazy brown with a medium tan head.  Aroma is very nutty with slight phenolic boozyness.  Flavor is big and rich bread malts, lots of caramel and toast with a sweet finish.
beer_name: Samuel Adams LongShot Derfs Secret Alt
